209 // Helpers: ImVec2/ImVec4 operators
210 // We are keeping those disabled by default so they don't leak in user space, to allow user enabling implicit cast operators between ImVec2 and their own types (using IM_VEC2_CLASS_EXTRA etc.)
211 // We unfortunately don't have a unary- operator for ImVec2 because this would needs to be defined inside the class itself.
212 #ifdef IMGUI_DEFINE_MATH_OPERATORS
213 static inline ImVec2 operator*(const ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x*rhs, lhs.y*rhs); }
214 static inline ImVec2 operator/(const ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x/rhs, lhs.y/rhs); }
215 static inline ImVec2 operator+(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x+rhs.x, lhs.y+rhs.y); }
216 static inline ImVec2 operator-(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x-rhs.x, lhs.y-rhs.y); }
217 static inline ImVec2 operator*(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x*rhs.x, lhs.y*rhs.y); }
218 static inline ImVec2 operator/(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x/rhs.x, lhs.y/rhs.y); }
219 static inline ImVec2& operator+=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x += rhs.x; lhs.y += rhs.y; return lhs; }
220 static inline ImVec2& operator-=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x -= rhs.x; lhs.y -= rhs.y; return lhs; }
221 static inline ImVec2& operator*=(ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { lhs.x *= rhs; lhs.y *= rhs; return lhs; }
222 static inline ImVec2& operator/=(ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { lhs.x /= rhs; lhs.y /= rhs; return lhs; }
223 static inline ImVec4 operator+(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x+rhs.x, lhs.y+rhs.y, lhs.z+rhs.z, lhs.w+rhs.w); }
224 static inline ImVec4 operator-(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x-rhs.x, lhs.y-rhs.y, lhs.z-rhs.z, lhs.w-rhs.w); }
225 static inline ImVec4 operator*(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x*rhs.x, lhs.y*rhs.y, lhs.z*rhs.z, lhs.w*rhs.w); }
226 #endif

232 static inline float ImSqrt(float x) { return sqrtf(x); }
233 static inline float ImPow(float x, float y) { return powf(x, y); }

235 static inline float ImFmod(float x, float y) { return fmodf(x, y); }

237 static inline float ImCos(float x) { return cosf(x); }
238 static inline float ImSin(float x) { return sinf(x); }
239 static inline float ImAcos(float x) { return acosf(x); }
240 static inline float ImAtan2(float y, float x) { return atan2f(y, x); }
241 static inline double ImAtof(const char* s) { return atof(s); }
242 static inline float ImFloorStd(float x) { return floorf(x); } // we already uses our own ImFloor() { return (float)(int)v } internally so the standard one wrapper is named differently (it's used by stb_truetype)
243 static inline float ImCeil(float x) { return ceilf(x); }
244 #endif
245 // - ImMin/ImMax/ImClamp/ImLerp/ImSwap are used by widgets which support for variety of types: signed/unsigned int/long long float/double
246 // (Exceptionally using templates here but we could also redefine them for variety of types)
247 template<typename T> static inline T ImMin(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs < rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
248 template<typename T> static inline T ImMax(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs >= rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
249 template<typename T> static inline T ImClamp(T v, T mn, T mx) { return (v < mn) ? mn : (v > mx) ? mx : v; }
250 template<typename T> static inline T ImLerp(T a, T b, float t) { return (T)(a + (b - a) * t); }
251 template<typename T> static inline void ImSwap(T& a, T& b) { T tmp = a; a = b; b = tmp; }
252 template<typename T> static inline T ImAddClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b < 0 && (a < mn - b)) return mn; if (b > 0 && (a > mx - b)) return mx; return a + b; }
253 template<typename T> static inline T ImSubClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b > 0 && (a < mn + b)) return mn; if (b < 0 && (a > mx + b)) return mx; return a - b; }
254 // - Misc maths helpers
255 static inline ImVec2 ImMin(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x < rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y < rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
256 static inline ImVec2 ImMax(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x >= rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y >= rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
257 static inline ImVec2 ImClamp(const ImVec2& v, const ImVec2& mn, ImVec2 mx) { return ImVec2((v.x < mn.x) ? mn.x : (v.x > mx.x) ? mx.x : v.x, (v.y < mn.y) ? mn.y : (v.y > mx.y) ? mx.y : v.y); }
258 static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, float t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t); }
259 static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, const ImVec2& t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t.x, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t.y); }
260 static inline ImVec4 ImLerp(const ImVec4& a, const ImVec4& b, float t) { return ImVec4(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t, a.z + (b.z - a.z) * t, a.w + (b.w - a.w) * t); }
261 static inline float ImSaturate(float f) { return (f < 0.0f) ? 0.0f : (f > 1.0f) ? 1.0f : f; }
262 static inline float ImLengthSqr(const ImVec2& lhs) { return lhs.x*lhs.x + lhs.y*lhs.y; }
263 static inline float ImLengthSqr(const ImVec4& lhs) { return lhs.x*lhs.x + lhs.y*lhs.y + lhs.z*lhs.z + lhs.w*lhs.w; }
264 static inline float ImInvLength(const ImVec2& lhs, float fail_value) { float d = lhs.x*lhs.x + lhs.y*lhs.y; if (d > 0.0f) return 1.0f / ImSqrt(d); return fail_value; }
265 static inline float ImFloor(float f) { return (float)(int)f; }
266 static inline ImVec2 ImFloor(const ImVec2& v) { return ImVec2((float)(int)v.x, (float)(int)v.y); }
267 static inline int ImModPositive(int a, int b) { return (a + b) % b; }
268 static inline float ImDot(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b) { return a.x * b.x + a.y * b.y; }
269 static inline ImVec2 ImRotate(const ImVec2& v, float cos_a, float sin_a) { return ImVec2(v.x * cos_a - v.y * sin_a, v.x * sin_a + v.y * cos_a); }
270 static inline float ImLinearSweep(float current, float target, float speed) { if (current < target) return ImMin(current + speed, target); if (current > target) return ImMax(current - speed, target); return current; }
271 static inline ImVec2 ImMul(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y); }

273 // Helper: ImBoolVector. Store 1-bit per value.
274 // Note that Resize() currently clears the whole vector.
275 struct ImBoolVector
276 {
277  ImVector<int> Storage;
278  ImBoolVector() { }
279  void Resize(int sz) { Storage.resize((sz + 31) >> 5); memset(Storage.Data, 0, (size_t)Storage.Size * sizeof(Storage.Data[0])); }
280  void Clear() { Storage.clear(); }
281  bool GetBit(int n) const { int off = (n >> 5); int mask = 1 << (n & 31); return (Storage[off] & mask) != 0; }
282  void SetBit(int n, bool v) { int off = (n >> 5); int mask = 1 << (n & 31); if (v) Storage[off] |= mask; else Storage[off] &= ~mask; }
283 };
284 
285 // Helper: ImPool<>. Basic keyed storage for contiguous instances, slow/amortized insertion, O(1) indexable, O(Log N) queries by ID over a dense/hot buffer,
286 // Honor constructor/destructor. Add/remove invalidate all pointers. Indexes have the same lifetime as the associated object.
287 typedef int ImPoolIdx;
288 template<typename T>
289 struct IMGUI_API ImPool
290 {
291  ImVector<T> Data; // Contiguous data
292  ImGuiStorage Map; // ID->Index
293  ImPoolIdx FreeIdx; // Next free idx to use
294 
295  ImPool() { FreeIdx = 0; }
296  ~ImPool() { Clear(); }
297  T* GetByKey(ImGuiID key) { int idx = Map.GetInt(key, -1); return (idx != -1) ? &Data[idx] : NULL; }
298  T* GetByIndex(ImPoolIdx n) { return &Data[n]; }
299  ImPoolIdx GetIndex(const T* p) const { IM_ASSERT(p >= Data.Data && p < Data.Data + Data.Size); return (ImPoolIdx)(p - Data.Data); }
300  T* GetOrAddByKey(ImGuiID key) { int* p_idx = Map.GetIntRef(key, -1); if (*p_idx != -1) return &Data[*p_idx]; *p_idx = FreeIdx; return Add(); }
301  bool Contains(const T* p) const { return (p >= Data.Data && p < Data.Data + Data.Size); }
302  void Clear() { for (int n = 0; n < Map.Data.Size; n++) { int idx = Map.Data[n].val_i; if (idx != -1) Data[idx].~T(); } Map.Clear(); Data.clear(); FreeIdx = 0; }
303  T* Add() { int idx = FreeIdx; if (idx == Data.Size) { Data.resize(Data.Size + 1); FreeIdx++; } else { FreeIdx = *(int*)&Data[idx]; } IM_PLACEMENT_NEW(&Data[idx]) T(); return &Data[idx]; }
304  void Remove(ImGuiID key, const T* p) { Remove(key, GetIndex(p)); }
305  void Remove(ImGuiID key, ImPoolIdx idx) { Data[idx].~T(); *(int*)&Data[idx] = FreeIdx; FreeIdx = idx; Map.SetInt(key, -1); }
306  void Reserve(int capacity) { Data.reserve(capacity); Map.Data.reserve(capacity); }
307  int GetSize() const { return Data.Size; }
308 };

314 enum ImGuiButtonFlags_
315 {
316  ImGuiButtonFlags_None = 0,
317  ImGuiButtonFlags_Repeat = 1 << 0, // hold to repeat
318  ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClickRelease = 1 << 1, // [Default] return true on click + release on same item
319  ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnClick = 1 << 2, // return true on click (default requires click+release)
320  ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnRelease = 1 << 3, // return true on release (default requires click+release)
321  ImGuiButtonFlags_PressedOnDoubleClick = 1 << 4, // return true on double-click (default requires click+release)
322  ImGuiButtonFlags_FlattenChildren = 1 << 5, // allow interactions even if a child window is overlapping
323  ImGuiButtonFlags_AllowItemOverlap = 1 << 6, // require previous frame HoveredId to either match id or be null before being usable, use along with SetItemAllowOverlap()
324  ImGuiButtonFlags_DontClosePopups = 1 << 7, // disable automatically closing parent popup on press // [UNUSED]
325  ImGuiButtonFlags_Disabled = 1 << 8, // disable interactions
326  ImGuiButtonFlags_AlignTextBaseLine = 1 << 9, // vertically align button to match text baseline - ButtonEx() only // FIXME: Should be removed and handled by SmallButton(), not possible currently because of DC.CursorPosPrevLine

541 // 2D axis aligned bounding-box
542 // NB: we can't rely on ImVec2 math operators being available here
543 struct IMGUI_API ImRect
544 {
545  ImVec2 Min; // Upper-left
546  ImVec2 Max; // Lower-right
547 
548  ImRect() : Min(FLT_MAX,FLT_MAX), Max(-FLT_MAX,-FLT_MAX) {}
549  ImRect(const ImVec2& min, const ImVec2& max) : Min(min), Max(max) {}
550  ImRect(const ImVec4& v) : Min(v.x, v.y), Max(v.z, v.w) {}
551  ImRect(float x1, float y1, float x2, float y2) : Min(x1, y1), Max(x2, y2) {}
552 
553  ImVec2 GetCenter() const { return ImVec2((Min.x + Max.x) * 0.5f, (Min.y + Max.y) * 0.5f); }
554  ImVec2 GetSize() const { return ImVec2(Max.x - Min.x, Max.y - Min.y); }
555  float GetWidth() const { return Max.x - Min.x; }
556  float GetHeight() const { return Max.y - Min.y; }
557  ImVec2 GetTL() const { return Min; } // Top-left
558  ImVec2 GetTR() const { return ImVec2(Max.x, Min.y); } // Top-right
559  ImVec2 GetBL() const { return ImVec2(Min.x, Max.y); } // Bottom-left
560  ImVec2 GetBR() const { return Max; } // Bottom-right
561  bool Contains(const ImVec2& p) const { return p.x >= Min.x && p.y >= Min.y && p.x < Max.x && p.y < Max.y; }
562  bool Contains(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.x >= Min.x && r.Min.y >= Min.y && r.Max.x <= Max.x && r.Max.y <= Max.y; }
563  bool Overlaps(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.y < Max.y && r.Max.y > Min.y && r.Min.x < Max.x && r.Max.x > Min.x; }
564  void Add(const ImVec2& p) { if (Min.x > p.x) Min.x = p.x; if (Min.y > p.y) Min.y = p.y; if (Max.x < p.x) Max.x = p.x; if (Max.y < p.y) Max.y = p.y; }
565  void Add(const ImRect& r) { if (Min.x > r.Min.x) Min.x = r.Min.x; if (Min.y > r.Min.y) Min.y = r.Min.y; if (Max.x < r.Max.x) Max.x = r.Max.x; if (Max.y < r.Max.y) Max.y = r.Max.y; }
566  void Expand(const float amount) { Min.x -= amount; Min.y -= amount; Max.x += amount; Max.y += amount; }
567  void Expand(const ImVec2& amount) { Min.x -= amount.x; Min.y -= amount.y; Max.x += amount.x; Max.y += amount.y; }
568  void Translate(const ImVec2& d) { Min.x += d.x; Min.y += d.y; Max.x += d.x; Max.y += d.y; }
569  void TranslateX(float dx) { Min.x += dx; Max.x += dx; }
570  void TranslateY(float dy) { Min.y += dy; Max.y += dy; }
571  void ClipWith(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImMax(Min, r.Min); Max = ImMin(Max, r.Max); } // Simple version, may lead to an inverted rectangle, which is fine for Contains/Overlaps test but not for display.
572  void ClipWithFull(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImClamp(Min, r.Min, r.Max); Max = ImClamp(Max, r.Min, r.Max); } // Full version, ensure both points are fully clipped.
573  void Floor() { Min.x = IM_FLOOR(Min.x); Min.y = IM_FLOOR(Min.y); Max.x = IM_FLOOR(Max.x); Max.y = IM_FLOOR(Max.y); }
574  bool IsInverted() const { return Min.x > Max.x || Min.y > Max.y; }
575 };
576

629 // Internal state of the currently focused/edited text input box
630 struct IMGUI_API ImGuiInputTextState
631 {
632  ImGuiID ID; // widget id owning the text state
633  int CurLenW, CurLenA; // we need to maintain our buffer length in both UTF-8 and wchar format. UTF-8 len is valid even if TextA is not.
634  ImVector<ImWchar> TextW; // edit buffer, we need to persist but can't guarantee the persistence of the user-provided buffer. so we copy into own buffer.
635  ImVector<char> TextA; // temporary UTF8 buffer for callbacks and other operations. this is not updated in every code-path! size=capacity.
636  ImVector<char> InitialTextA; // backup of end-user buffer at the time of focus (in UTF-8, unaltered)
637  bool TextAIsValid; // temporary UTF8 buffer is not initially valid before we make the widget active (until then we pull the data from user argument)
638  int BufCapacityA; // end-user buffer capacity
639  float ScrollX; // horizontal scrolling/offset
640  ImStb::STB_TexteditState Stb; // state for stb_textedit.h
641  float CursorAnim; // timer for cursor blink, reset on every user action so the cursor reappears immediately
642  bool CursorFollow; // set when we want scrolling to follow the current cursor position (not always!)
643  bool SelectedAllMouseLock; // after a double-click to select all, we ignore further mouse drags to update selection
644  ImGuiInputTextFlags UserFlags; // Temporarily set while we call user's callback
645  ImGuiInputTextCallback UserCallback; // "
646  void* UserCallbackData; // "
647 
648  ImGuiInputTextState() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
649  void ClearText() { CurLenW = CurLenA = 0; TextW[0] = 0; TextA[0] = 0; CursorClamp(); }
650  void ClearFreeMemory() { TextW.clear(); TextA.clear(); InitialTextA.clear(); }
651  int GetUndoAvailCount() const { return Stb.undostate.undo_point; }
652  int GetRedoAvailCount() const { return STB_TEXTEDIT_UNDOSTATECOUNT - Stb.undostate.redo_point; }
653  void OnKeyPressed(int key); // Cannot be inline because we call in code in stb_textedit.h implementation
654 
655  // Cursor & Selection
656  void CursorAnimReset() { CursorAnim = -0.30f; } // After a user-input the cursor stays on for a while without blinking
657  void CursorClamp() { Stb.cursor = ImMin(Stb.cursor, CurLenW); Stb.select_start = ImMin(Stb.select_start, CurLenW); Stb.select_end = ImMin(Stb.select_end, CurLenW); }
658  bool HasSelection() const { return Stb.select_start != Stb.select_end; }
659  void ClearSelection() { Stb.select_start = Stb.select_end = Stb.cursor; }
660  void SelectAll() { Stb.select_start = 0; Stb.cursor = Stb.select_end = CurLenW; Stb.has_preferred_x = 0; }
661 };

846 struct ImGuiPtrOrIndex
847 {
848  void* Ptr; // Either field can be set, not both. e.g. Dock node tab bars are loose while BeginTabBar() ones are in a pool.
849  int Index; // Usually index in a main pool.
850 
851  ImGuiPtrOrIndex(void* ptr) { Ptr = ptr; Index = -1; }
852  ImGuiPtrOrIndex(int index) { Ptr = NULL; Index = index; }
853 };

1202 // Transient per-window data, reset at the beginning of the frame. This used to be called ImGuiDrawContext, hence the DC variable name in ImGuiWindow.
1203 // FIXME: That's theory, in practice the delimitation between ImGuiWindow and ImGuiWindowTempData is quite tenuous and could be reconsidered.
1204 struct IMGUI_API ImGuiWindowTempData
1205 {
1206  ImVec2 CursorPos; // Current emitting position, in absolute coordinates.
1207  ImVec2 CursorPosPrevLine;
1208  ImVec2 CursorStartPos; // Initial position after Begin(), generally ~ window position + WindowPadding.
1209  ImVec2 CursorMaxPos; // Used to implicitly calculate the size of our contents, always growing during the frame. Used to calculate window->ContentSize at the beginning of next frame
1210  ImVec2 CurrLineSize;
1211  ImVec2 PrevLineSize;
1212  float CurrLineTextBaseOffset; // Baseline offset (0.0f by default on a new line, generally == style.FramePadding.y when a framed item has been added).
1213  float PrevLineTextBaseOffset;
1214  int TreeDepth; // Current tree depth.
1215  ImU32 TreeMayJumpToParentOnPopMask; // Store a copy of !g.NavIdIsAlive for TreeDepth 0..31.. Could be turned into a ImU64 if necessary.
1216  ImGuiID LastItemId; // ID for last item
1217  ImGuiItemStatusFlags LastItemStatusFlags; // Status flags for last item (see ImGuiItemStatusFlags_)
1218  ImRect LastItemRect; // Interaction rect for last item
1219  ImRect LastItemDisplayRect; // End-user display rect for last item (only valid if LastItemStatusFlags & ImGuiItemStatusFlags_HasDisplayRect)
1220  ImGuiNavLayer NavLayerCurrent; // Current layer, 0..31 (we currently only use 0..1)
1221  int NavLayerCurrentMask; // = (1 << NavLayerCurrent) used by ItemAdd prior to clipping.
1222  int NavLayerActiveMask; // Which layer have been written to (result from previous frame)
1223  int NavLayerActiveMaskNext; // Which layer have been written to (buffer for current frame)
1224  bool NavHideHighlightOneFrame;
1225  bool NavHasScroll; // Set when scrolling can be used (ScrollMax > 0.0f)
1226  bool MenuBarAppending; // FIXME: Remove this
1227  ImVec2 MenuBarOffset; // MenuBarOffset.x is sort of equivalent of a per-layer CursorPos.x, saved/restored as we switch to the menu bar. The only situation when MenuBarOffset.y is > 0 if when (SafeAreaPadding.y > FramePadding.y), often used on TVs.
1228  ImVector<ImGuiWindow*> ChildWindows;
1229  ImGuiStorage* StateStorage; // Current persistent per-window storage (store e.g. tree node open/close state)
1230  ImGuiLayoutType LayoutType;
1231  ImGuiLayoutType ParentLayoutType; // Layout type of parent window at the time of Begin()
1232  int FocusCounterAll; // Counter for focus/tabbing system. Start at -1 and increase as assigned via FocusableItemRegister() (FIXME-NAV: Needs redesign)
1233  int FocusCounterTab; // (same, but only count widgets which you can Tab through)
1234 
1235  // We store the current settings outside of the vectors to increase memory locality (reduce cache misses). The vectors are rarely modified. Also it allows us to not heap allocate for short-lived windows which are not using those settings.
1236  ImGuiItemFlags ItemFlags; // == ItemFlagsStack.back() [empty == ImGuiItemFlags_Default]
1237  float ItemWidth; // == ItemWidthStack.back(). 0.0: default, >0.0: width in pixels, <0.0: align xx pixels to the right of window
1238  float TextWrapPos; // == TextWrapPosStack.back() [empty == -1.0f]
1239  ImVector<ImGuiItemFlags>ItemFlagsStack;
1240  ImVector<float> ItemWidthStack;
1241  ImVector<float> TextWrapPosStack;
1242  ImVector<ImGuiGroupData>GroupStack;
1243  short StackSizesBackup[6]; // Store size of various stacks for asserting
1244 
1245  ImVec1 Indent; // Indentation / start position from left of window (increased by TreePush/TreePop, etc.)
1246  ImVec1 GroupOffset;
1247  ImVec1 ColumnsOffset; // Offset to the current column (if ColumnsCurrent > 0). FIXME: This and the above should be a stack to allow use cases like Tree->Column->Tree. Need revamp columns API.
1248  ImGuiColumns* CurrentColumns; // Current columns set
1249 
1250  ImGuiWindowTempData()
1251  {
1252  CursorPos = CursorPosPrevLine = CursorStartPos = CursorMaxPos = ImVec2(0.0f, 0.0f);
1253  CurrLineSize = PrevLineSize = ImVec2(0.0f, 0.0f);
1254  CurrLineTextBaseOffset = PrevLineTextBaseOffset = 0.0f;
1255  TreeDepth = 0;
1256  TreeMayJumpToParentOnPopMask = 0x00;
1257  LastItemId = 0;
1258  LastItemStatusFlags = 0;
1259  LastItemRect = LastItemDisplayRect = ImRect();
1260  NavLayerActiveMask = NavLayerActiveMaskNext = 0x00;
1261  NavLayerCurrent = ImGuiNavLayer_Main;
1262  NavLayerCurrentMask = (1 << ImGuiNavLayer_Main);
1263  NavHideHighlightOneFrame = false;
1264  NavHasScroll = false;
1265  MenuBarAppending = false;
1266  MenuBarOffset = ImVec2(0.0f, 0.0f);
1267  StateStorage = NULL;
1268  LayoutType = ParentLayoutType = ImGuiLayoutType_Vertical;
1269  FocusCounterAll = FocusCounterTab = -1;
1270 
1271  ItemFlags = ImGuiItemFlags_Default_;
1272  ItemWidth = 0.0f;
1273  TextWrapPos = -1.0f;
1274  memset(StackSizesBackup, 0, sizeof(StackSizesBackup));
1275 
1276  Indent = ImVec1(0.0f);
1277  GroupOffset = ImVec1(0.0f);
1278  ColumnsOffset = ImVec1(0.0f);
1279  CurrentColumns = NULL;
1280  }
1281 };

1283 // Storage for one window
1284 struct IMGUI_API ImGuiWindow
1285 {
1286  char* Name;
1287  ImGuiID ID; // == ImHash(Name)
1288  ImGuiWindowFlags Flags; // See enum ImGuiWindowFlags_
1289  ImVec2 Pos; // Position (always rounded-up to nearest pixel)
1290  ImVec2 Size; // Current size (==SizeFull or collapsed title bar size)
1291  ImVec2 SizeFull; // Size when non collapsed
1292  ImVec2 ContentSize; // Size of contents/scrollable client area (calculated from the extents reach of the cursor) from previous frame. Does not include window decoration or window padding.
1293  ImVec2 ContentSizeExplicit; // Size of contents/scrollable client area explicitly request by the user via SetNextWindowContentSize().
1294  ImVec2 WindowPadding; // Window padding at the time of Begin().
1295  float WindowRounding; // Window rounding at the time of Begin().
1296  float WindowBorderSize; // Window border size at the time of Begin().

1479  // We should always have a CurrentWindow in the stack (there is an implicit "Debug" window)
1480  // If this ever crash because g.CurrentWindow is NULL it means that either
1481  // - ImGui::NewFrame() has never been called, which is illegal.
1482  // - You are calling ImGui functions after ImGui::EndFrame()/ImGui::Render() and before the next ImGui::NewFrame(), which is also illegal.
1483  inline ImGuiWindow* GetCurrentWindowRead() { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; return g.CurrentWindow; }
